<span id="freeTextContainer10141754105569207070"><b> &quot;Each century brought its share of shadow and light, apathy and combat, truth and error, and its courtship of systems, new ideas, new illusions.&quot; </b><br/><br/><img src='https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1595786286i/29863672._SY540_.jpg' width='240' height='480' alt='description' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/><br/>First time reading anything by Machado de Assis. This was my first time being introduced to the Brazilian Literature and that was with our book club.<br/><br/>This book is so funny and was written really well. Starting from the opposite way, Death.<br/>The story of Brás Cubas and all encounters with humans through family, friendships, and even love.<br/><br/>I didn&apos;t like Vir</span>
